---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Can I use this for vibe coding?",
    a: `Absolutely. Nudgy was basically built for vibe coding sessions.

When you're deep in a flow with Claude or Cursor, being able to capture your screen, circle the thing that's broken, and paste it straight into the chat is a superpower. No descriptions, no misunderstandings. Just point at the problem.

Vibe coding moves fast. Nudgy keeps up.`,
  },
  {
    q: "Which AI tools will it work with?",
    a: `All the major ones. Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini, and Cursor are all multimodal and handle images natively. Just paste or attach your annotated screenshot and you're good to go.

It also works with AI-powered command line tools. Claude Code in Terminal, for example, can read images directly, so you can drop an annotated screenshot straight into your CLI workflow.

If an AI tool has an image input, Nudgy works with it.`,
  },
  {
    q: "Will AI actually work with these screenshots?",
    a: `Yes, and in most cases it works better than typing out a long prompt.

Describing a UI bug or layout issue in words is slow and ambiguous. An annotated screenshot cuts straight to the point. Your AI sees exactly what you see, with your arrows and notes pointing at the problem.

Less back-and-forth, fewer misunderstandings. Just faster, clearer results.`,
  },
  {
    q: "Why not just use macOS's built-in screenshot tools?",
    a: `macOS is great at capturing. But the moment you need to circle something, draw an arrow, or write "THIS" next to a bug, you're opening another app and losing your flow.

Nudgy keeps you in the zone. Capture, annotate, copy, done. No context switching, no friction.`,
  },
  {
    q: "Is my data actually private?",
    a: `Completely. Nudgy runs entirely on your Mac. No server, no account, no analytics. Your screenshots never leave your machine.

We literally have no way to see them even if we wanted to.`,
  },
  {
    q: "How fast is it really?",
    a: `From shortcut to annotated screenshot in your clipboard: under 10 seconds if you're taking your time. The global shortcut means you never have to leave whatever you're working on.

Capture. Annotate. Paste. Done.`,
  },
  {
    q: "Who is Nudgy for?",
    a: `Anyone who communicates visually: teammates, clients, or AI tools.

If you've ever typed three paragraphs trying to describe something you could have just circled, Nudgy is for you.`,
  },
];
---

<section class="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <p class="eyebrow">For Humans and AI</p>
      <h2 class="heading">FAQ</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="list">
      {faqs.map((item) => (
        <details class="item">
          <summary class="question">
            <span>{item.q}</span>
            <svg class="chevron" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
              <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/>
            </svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="answer">
            <div class="answer-inner">
              {item.a.split('\n\n').map((para) => (
                <p>{para}</p>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLDetailsElement>('details.item').forEach(details => {
    const summary = details.querySelector('summary')!;
    const answer = details.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.answer')!;

    summary.addEventListener('click', e => {
      e.preventDefault();
      if (details.open) {
        answer.style.maxHeight = answer.scrollHeight + 'px';
        requestAnimationFrame(() => { answer.style.maxHeight = '0'; });
        answer.addEventListener('transitionend', () => { details.open = false; }, { once: true });
      } else {
        details.open = true;
        answer.style.maxHeight = '0';
        requestAnimationFrame(() => { answer.style.maxHeight = answer.scrollHeight + 'px'; });
        answer.addEventListener('transitionend', () => { answer.style.maxHeight = ''; }, { once: true });
      }
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  .faq {
    padding: 5rem 1.5rem 6rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .section-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .heading {
    font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 3.5vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    line-height: 1.12;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .item {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .item:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .question {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 0;
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .question::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }

  .question:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .chevron {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    color: var(--muted);
    transition: transform 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);
  }

  .item[open] .chevron {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }

  .item[open] .question {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .answer {
    overflow: hidden;
    max-height: 0;
    transition: max-height 0.35s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);
  }

  .item[open] .answer {
    max-height: 600px;
  }

  .answer-inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.85rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .answer p {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
</style>
